1.5.2024 - engaged to the man of my dreams ❤️ 
my favorite guy surprised me with a proposal beyond my dreams at a penthouse suite at the Plaza Hotel!! (more on the room and the surprise in another post bc it was unreal 😭) I couldn't have asked for a better partner. I love you so much, Milton. I am my best version with you. Thank you for making me the happiest girl in the world. Here's to together forever ❤️

Special shout out to my best friends, @mysha_azzad , @aiyanaalewis , and  @olivviamarie for keeping the surprise, making sure I was ready and in the perfect dress! Also to Milan's brother, Sajan, for taking me to the destination and keeping up the lies lol and thank you @max_greenberg_ for being Milan's wingman (: And finally, thank you to my best friend @aprilguven for making my dream ring 😭😭 love everyone who was involved so much! I'll save the story time for the next post (:

He finally put a ring on it and did it in the most special way at the most iconic place 🥹 @theplazahotel still not over how stunning this room was ❤️

#nycproposal #isaidyes💍 #proposalideas #howheasked #nycwedding  #dreamproposal

PROPOSAL STORY: so Milan told me a week before the proposal that we were going to a gala. I was already suspicious because he didn't mention the charity or send me an invitation like he usually does. I didn't really know for sure until his brother texted me the night before and said he is going to the gala too and that he will be picking me up. I asked his brother if I should wear white and he said yes lol you can't wear white to a black tie event so that's when I knew for sure! Friday afternoon, he picked me up and took me to this hotel on Central Park. It was a cute hotel but he said we were in the wrong spot and the real location is walking distance. We then start walking and I realize we are at THE PLAZA HOTEL!! The concierge meets us in the lobby and then takes us to the elevator and hits the penthouse floor?? I'm still confused like is there a terrace up there? But no Milan actually booked at penthouse suite!! I was shocked when the concierge opened the door and there were rose petals leading into the room, up the stairs, and out the balcony. I walked to the balcony and there Milan was. When I saw him, he said "are you ready for gala?" 😂 then he gave his speech and did it 🥹 afterwards we took pictures and obsessed over the suite and I realized I would be staying the night here! I didn't have any clothes so my roommate and best friend came to drop off a night bag for me (an angel). She and other family members stayed at the suite with us for a bit so we could celebrate more (: I honestly could have never dreamt of a better proposal 🥹
